
[1]counterguard

   COUNTERGUARD,n. [counter and guard.] In fortification, a small rampart
   or work raised before the point of a bastion, consisting of two long
   faces parallel to the faces of the bastion, making a salient angle, to
   preserve the bastion. It is sometimes of a different shape, or
   differently situated.
